@item Events in
@table @code

@item @eventServerNotifyReg 
from @procClientMisc{}: ask notify by setting a value into share memory and sending a signal.

@item @eventServerNotifyQuery 
from a remote @process{notify} process: receive a socket query providing remote cache content index.

@end table
@item Processing

@itemize @bullet
@item 
The policy is, sender servers tells each others:
@itemize @bullet
@item final demands they have to extract,
@item local supplies (presently into theire cache) that may be useful to others or are unsafe.
@end itemize
@item
However:
@itemize @bullet
@item servers do not try to send messages to unreachable @acronym{NAT}'s client servers,
@item @acronym{NAT} client servers do not send messages to servers that cannot reach them.
@end itemize
@item
So, @acronym{NAT} gateway servers do:
@itemize @bullet
@item forward messages unchanged to its @acronym{NAT}'s client servers,
@item relay (doing masquerade) final demands of its @acronym{NAT}'s client servers.
@item
Receiver server returns @code{240}.
@end itemize

@end itemize

